body:
Hi,
I'm writing in regards to an issue I faced with the instantsearch and after spending days on trying to solve the problem I still can't get my head around it, maybe I missed something from the documentation.

Basically I want to build some dropdowns on a homepage with the data coming from algolia, and when the user clicks on a search button send him to a results page. 
The search needs to take football team code as opposed to a name.

Let me explain you my problem by showing you how the data is structured in algolia, this by the way is mock data.
```js
// Algolia Object structure
"footballTeams": [
	{
		"code": "FCB",
		"name": "Barcelona"
	},{
		"code": "RMA",
		"name": "Real Madrid"
	},{
		"code": "JUV",
		"name": "Torino Juventus"
	},
]

// This is how I'd like my dropdown to look like:
/* < select>
     < option value="FCB">Barcelona</ option>
	< option value="RMA">Real Madrid</ option>
	< option value="JUV">Torino Juventus</ option>
 </ select>*/

// This is how I'm building my widget
search.addWidget(
	instantsearch.widgets.customSelectorWidget({
		container: '#footballteams',
		attributeName: 'footballTeams'		
}));  

// Custom selector widget
instantsearch.widgets.customSelectorWidget = function customSelectorWidget(options) {
	var container = options.container;
    var attributeName = options.attributeName;
	
	return {
		getConfiguration: function getConfiguration() {
            return {					
                hierarchicalFacets: [
                    {
                        name: attributeName,
                        attributes: [attributeName]
                    }
                ]
            };
		},
		init: function init(options) {
			
		},
		render: function render(options) {
			var facetValues = results.getFacetValues(attributeName, { sortBy: sortBy }).data;
                        // some more code here to build the dropdowns
		}
	}
}
```

In the render bit when calling results.getFacetValues I'm expecting the results to come back like this(or similar):
```js
"footballTeams": [
	{code: "FCB",name: "Barcelona", count: 1, isRefined: false},
	{code: "RMA",name: "Real Madrid", count: 1, isRefined: false},
	{code: "JUV",name: "Torino Juventus", count: 1, isRefined: false},
]
```
but instead I get null back.

Any suggestions on how to solve this?

Thank you very much
